The popular fruits market in Nigeria, Ketu -Mile 12, in Ikosi-Isheri Local Council Development, LCDA, has been demolished to pave way for its redevelopment into a modern market. Heavily armed special taskforce personnel were seen at the site about 11 am, bringing down the structures. There were sporadic shootings by armed policemen when some miscreants and traders put up resistance as they started throwing pebbles and broken bottles at the task team. Demolition is currently ongoing.  Details still to come